Mommy missed her train.

83
00:12:26,706 --> 00:12:28,126
Ice.

84
00:12:29,087 --> 00:12:31,587
About an hour.

85
00:12:32,797 --> 00:12:34,717
You should start your homework.

86
00:12:35,677 --> 00:12:40,267
I promise to tell you all about it
when I see you. I love you. Bye.

87
00:12:41,888 --> 00:12:46,898
That was my son, Charlie.
He's 8. He'll be 9 next week.

88
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:51,318
I'm Paul Martel. I'll be 28 in July.

89
00:12:51,819 --> 00:12:56,199
I'm Constance.
And I'm late. I have to go.

90
00:12:56,910 --> 00:13:00,660
Before you go, take a book.

91
00:13:00,910 --> 00:13:05,420
No. I couldn't.

92
00:13:05,711 --> 00:13:09,131
Sure you can. A souvenir.

93
00:13:09,381 --> 00:13:12,881
Go down there. You know, like before.

94
00:13:13,131 --> 00:13:14,971
Okay.

95
00:13:22,933 --> 00:13:26,313
Keep going. Stop.

96
00:13:26,853 --> 00:13:28,403
Now right.

97
00:13:28,653 --> 00:13:30,823
No, right.

98
00:13:32,114 --> 00:13:36,154
Okay, now the second shelf
from the top. . .

99
00:13:36,364 --> 00:13:39,164
. . .take the fourth one from the left.

100
00:13:39,415 --> 00:13:41,335
Got it?

101
00:13:41,876 --> 00:13:45,126
- Think so.
- Open to page 23.

102
00:13:53,516 --> 00:13:57,846
Drink wine, this is life eternal

103
00:13:58,057 --> 00:14:01,397
This, all that youth will give to you

104
00:14:01,647 --> 00:14:06,397
It is the season for wine, roses
And drunken friends

105
00:14:06,648 --> 00:14:08,698
Be happy for this moment

106
00:14:08,909 --> 00:14:12,369
This moment is your life

107
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:24,630
I have to go. Thank you.

108
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:28,470
- Can you find your way out?
- I hope so.

109
00:14:30,591 --> 00:14:32,511
That's my bedroom.

110
00:14:35,312 --> 00:14:38,852
It was nice meeting you, Constance.

111
00:14:39,522 --> 00:14:43,482
Come back if you need more books
or medical attention.

112
00:15:22,317 --> 00:15:24,487
Hey, Glo.

113
00:15:25,328 --> 00:15:29,538
- That wouldn't be the TV on, would it?
- I was just turning it off.

114
00:15:30,078 --> 00:15:32,288
Sure you were.

115
00:15:38,010 --> 00:15:40,420
- The wind knocked me down.
- Yeah?

116
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:43,300
You all right? You need anything?

117
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:49,980
- Gross. Were you in a fight?
- No, just fell over.

118
00:15:50,181 --> 00:15:52,391
- Does it hurt?
- Little bit.

119
00:15:52,641 --> 00:15:55,311
- Cool!
- Where are you going?

120
00:15:55,521 --> 00:15:59,191
- To get the camera!
- Try this.

121
00:16:00,903 --> 00:16:05,533
- Why do you need the camera?
- It's for school. We're doing blood.

122
00:16:05,783 --> 00:16:09,083
Okay, now look like it really hurts.

123
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:11,333
- Ready?
- Yeah.

124
00:16:13,874 --> 00:16:15,254
This will be great.

125
00:16:15,834 --> 00:16:19,764
The wind blew her down.
She bled and everything.

126
00:16:20,014 --> 00:16:23,974
- Everybody's hats blew off.
- Quite the war photographer. You okay?

127
00:16:24,225 --> 00:16:27,015
Yeah. It took me down
like an old lady.

128
00:16:27,226 --> 00:16:32,186
- It was humiliating.
- Dad, look at the pictures.

129
00:16:32,396 --> 00:16:35,236
At least we got the evidence.
Anyone we can sue?

130
00:16:35,446 --> 00:16:39,366
No. There was this nice guy
who helped me.

131
00:16:39,577 --> 00:16:42,787
It was like this, Dad.
It was a twister.

132
00:16:44,917 --> 00:16:48,207
Dad, look. It was like this.

133
00:16:48,418 --> 00:16:50,588
- Wow.
- It's a tornado.

134
00:16:50,839 --> 00:16:56,259
He lived around there. He got me
some Band-Aids and put me in a taxi.

135
00:16:56,509 --> 00:16:58,599
Was he good-looking?

136
00:17:01,639 --> 00:17:02,969
I feel sick.

137
00:17:03,730 --> 00:17:08,230
- You do your homework?
- I can't. I don't know how to do it.

138
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:12,610
Come on, I'll help you.
Then you can help me with mine.

139
00:17:12,861 --> 00:17:15,821
Did you get his name, this guy?

140
00:17:16,072 --> 00:17:18,742
We could send him a bottle of wine.

141
00:17:19,282 --> 00:17:21,452
Cheap wine.

142
00:17:36,974 --> 00:17:40,224
Con, stand there a second.
Wait a minute.

143
00:17:40,804 --> 00:17:44,394
Stay there a second.
I'm trying to figure out the. . . .

144
00:17:45,185 --> 00:17:49,315
The thing I can't figure out
is the zoom-thing.

145
00:17:49,565 --> 00:17:51,945
There it is.
Okay, hold on, stay there.

146
00:17:52,155 --> 00:17:56,365
Got the zoomy-thingy zooming.

147
00:17:58,367 --> 00:18:03,127
Stay there. I'm trying to figure
this out. I wanna see if it focuses.

148
00:18:08,008 --> 00:18:09,928
Cool. Very cool.

149
00:18:10,178 --> 00:18:13,388
So beautiful. If you only knew.

150
00:18:13,638 --> 00:18:17,638
Look at you. God, what a beauty.

151
00:18:26,530 --> 00:18:28,990
Something the matter?

152
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:35,080
Nothing. Nothing at all.

153
00:18:52,473 --> 00:18:56,853
- This is really good.
- No, it isn't. Go away.

154
00:19:01,484 --> 00:19:06,614
I think I'm really zooming.
I found the zoom. Found it.

155
00:19:06,824 --> 00:19:08,864
Dad.

156
00:19:09,115 --> 00:19:11,365
- Shit.
- Mom.

157
00:19:11,746 --> 00:19:14,876
I can't sleep.

158
00:19:18,836 --> 00:19:22,836
I'll be back. I'll be back.
Don't fall asleep.

159
00:19:23,137 --> 00:19:24,297
It works.

160
00:19:30,057 --> 00:19:33,977
Mom, are you nuts?
You forgot my lunch.

161
00:19:34,438 --> 00:19:38,438
I did not. It's by the door.
Come with me.

162
00:19:38,649 --> 00:19:41,699
- What are you chewing?
- Nothing.

163
00:19:41,949 --> 00:19:44,609
Spit that out. What is that?

164
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:50,040
- That's lovely.
- Mom?

165
00:19:50,290 --> 00:19:52,460
I don't want to be a dumb bunny.

166
00:19:52,710 --> 00:19:57,590
Honey, it's a play. There's lots
of other bunnies. It'll be cool.

167
00:19:58,131 --> 00:20:00,671
- You're bonkers, Mom.
- So you tell me.

168
00:20:00,922 --> 00:20:04,012
- Love you.
- Love you too. What's that?

169
00:20:04,262 --> 00:20:06,262
Thank you.

170
00:20:09,932 --> 00:20:10,972
Bye.

171
00:22:16,448 --> 00:22:21,538
Hi, this is Paul Martel. Leave
a message after the beep. Thanks.

172
00:22:22,879 --> 00:22:24,539
Hello? Hello?

173
00:22:25,129 --> 00:22:27,089
- Hello?
- Hello?

174
00:22:27,299 --> 00:22:29,759
You're there.

175
00:22:29,929 --> 00:22:33,549
This is Connie Sumner,
the one from the windy day.

176
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,310
Oh, that one.

177
00:22:37,310 --> 00:22:39,270
How's the knee? Did you ice it?

178
00:22:39,681 --> 00:22:43,691
Yes, I iced it and I elevated it.
You name it, I did it.

179
00:22:43,942 --> 00:22:49,282
It's much better.
I just wanted to call and thank you.

180
00:22:49,492 --> 00:22:52,202
I wanted your address
because I wanted...

181
00:22:52,452 --> 00:22:54,162
- Where are you?
- What?

182
00:22:54,412 --> 00:22:56,702
I said, where are you?

183
00:22:59,503 --> 00:23:02,873
I'm in Grand Central.
It's really hard to hear you.

184
00:23:03,174 --> 00:23:05,754
- Come and see me.
- What?

185
00:23:06,004 --> 00:23:09,384
Yeah, take a break.
I'll make you some coffee.

186
00:23:12,845 --> 00:23:14,765
Coffee?

187
00:23:21,025 --> 00:23:23,485
- Okay.
- Okay.

188
00:23:23,906 --> 00:23:25,486
See you. Bye.

189
00:23:25,696 --> 00:23:27,326
Fuck.

190
00:23:38,918 --> 00:23:41,838
No permanent damage, I see.

191
00:23:44,758 --> 00:23:49,428
- We take Medicaid, Blue Cross. . . .
- I'm uninsured.

192
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:53,690
No. I'm afraid we don't
take charity cases.

193
00:23:58,650 --> 00:24:00,650
It was a joke.

194
00:24:08,951 --> 00:24:12,201
Look at this. Jack London.

195
00:24:12,412 --> 00:24:16,252
First edition of White Fang,
in the original dust jacket.

196
00:24:17,083 --> 00:24:19,343
And I got it for a buck fifty.

197
00:24:19,543 --> 00:24:23,673
- What's it worth?
- About 4000 times more.

198
00:24:27,434 --> 00:24:32,524
- Those are in French.
- I took it in school.

199
00:24:37,446 --> 00:24:39,776
Do I want to take off something?

200
00:24:41,866 --> 00:24:46,076
Your coat. Would you like
to take off your coat?

201
00:24:46,326 --> 00:24:48,746
Yes, my coat.

202
00:24:49,246 --> 00:24:51,166
Thank you.

203
00:24:58,967 --> 00:25:03,427
But I can't stay very long.
I have some errands I have to run.

204
00:25:04,309 --> 00:25:07,439
- I'll get the coffee.
- Okay.

205
00:25:28,712 --> 00:25:32,382
- It's in Braille.
- Braille.

206
00:25:32,632 --> 00:25:35,632
No, no, Braille.
He was French.

207
00:25:36,922 --> 00:25:38,722
Close your eyes.

208
00:25:38,972 --> 00:25:42,472
- What?
- Close your eyes.

209
00:25:56,745 --> 00:25:59,995
My mother makes me chicken

210
00:26:02,705 --> 00:26:06,335
Her chicken makes me cough

211
00:26:07,706 --> 00:26:10,426
I wish that when she made it

212
00:26:11,217 --> 00:26:14,297
She took the feathers off

213
00:26:19,428 --> 00:26:22,018
It doesn't say that.

214
00:26:31,319 --> 00:26:33,909
- I had better go.
- Yeah?

215
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:36,370
I'd better go.

216
00:26:41,210 --> 00:26:43,380
Take care. Don't fall.

217
00:26:43,581 --> 00:26:48,761
- Thanks for the coffee.
- You didn't drink it.

218
00:27:04,943 --> 00:27:08,073
- Lindsay, hi.
- Connie.

219
00:27:08,323 --> 00:27:10,403
- Let me buzz him.
- Thanks.

220
00:27:13,114 --> 00:27:17,084
Hey, what a surprise. Look at you.

221
00:27:17,284 --> 00:27:18,914
- Hi, Bill.
- Hi, Connie.

222
00:27:19,124 --> 00:27:21,544
- Am I interrupting?
- No, I'm leaving.

223
00:27:21,796 --> 00:27:25,176
- I'll get you the budget later.
- All right, thanks.

224
00:27:25,426 --> 00:27:28,926
- Would you like a coffee?
- No, thank you.

225
00:27:34,807 --> 00:27:36,937
That's nice.

226
00:27:38,937 --> 00:27:42,027
I didn't know
you were coming in today.

227
00:27:42,277 --> 00:27:44,697
You're freezing.
What is that?

228
00:27:44,948 --> 00:27:48,448
I was around the corner
and I brought you a present.

229
00:27:48,659 --> 00:27:51,329
Wow. What's the occasion?

230
00:27:51,499 --> 00:27:54,369
Nothing. I don't know.

231
00:27:54,709 --> 00:27:58,129
It's a medium,
but they said it runs large.

232
00:27:58,669 --> 00:28:01,799
- Look at that.
- You don't have to try it on.

233
00:28:02,260 --> 00:28:05,300
I'm the boss.
I can do whatever I want.

234
00:28:13,022 --> 00:28:14,812
What do you think?

235
00:28:16,562 --> 00:28:18,902
Hold on just a second.

236
00:28:20,022 --> 00:28:21,782
Yeah?

237
00:28:23,692 --> 00:28:25,992
Okay, but hold the other calls.

238
00:28:26,703 --> 00:28:28,413
- You're busy. I'll go.
- Sit.

239
00:28:28,623 --> 00:28:30,743
- I'll go.
- No, sit.

240
00:28:31,124 --> 00:28:35,164
Hello, Henry?
So, what is this suspension problem?

241
00:28:35,414 --> 00:28:37,834
No, I never received it.

242
00:28:39,215 --> 00:28:42,255
Well, get it to me.

243
00:28:42,885 --> 00:28:47,435
It's not good enough. I'm sitting here
with 200 trucks I can't use.

244
00:28:47,685 --> 00:28:51,605
Well, set up a meeting.
And I want Frank Birnbaum there.

245
00:28:51,856 --> 00:28:56,606
Because when I tell someone
to do something, I want it done.

246
00:28:56,857 --> 00:28:58,697
I'm sure you will.

247
00:29:03,698 --> 00:29:06,658
So, what else you up to?

248
00:29:07,328 --> 00:29:11,248
- Auction.
- Yeah? Who'd you hit on?

249
00:29:13,588 --> 00:29:16,548
The usual suspects.

250
